Package alien4cloud.exception

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AlreadyExistException
    Exception to be thrown when trying to insert an existing an element that already exists.
    ApplicationVersionNotFoundException  
    CyclicReferenceException
    This exception is thrown when attempting to add a node in a topology that references the same topology (cyclic composition).
    DeleteDeployedException
    Thrown when a deployed environment / topology is about to be deleted
    DeleteLastApplicationEnvironmentException  
    DeleteLastApplicationVersionException  
    DeleteReferencedObjectException
    This exception should be thrown when attempting to delete an object in Alien which is still referenced (used) by other object
    FunctionalException
    All functional exception which is related to user input must go here.
    GitConflictException
    Exception to be thrown in case there is an issue with a git repository.
    GitException
    Exception to be thrown in case there is an issue with a git repository.
    GitMergingStateException
    Exception to be thrown in case there is an issue with a git repository.
    GitStateException
    Exception to be thrown in case there is an issue with a git repository.
    IndexingServiceException
    All errors happened while trying to access to index service
    InitializationException
    Exception to be thrown in case of an error that prevents alien to startup.
    InvalidArgumentException  
    InvalidNameException
    Generic exception to throw when the name is invalid.
    LocationSupportException
    Generic exception to throw when location support violation
    MissingCSARDependenciesException
    Exception to be thrown when trying create a location an parse an CSAR form plugin before this dependencies.
    NotFoundException  
    ReferencedResourceException
    Exception to be thrown when an operation cannot be done because a resource is used (referenced).
    ReleaseReferencingSnapshotException
    Thrown when attempting to create a release version of an application of a template while some dependencies remain in snapshot.
    RenameDeployedException  
    TechnicalException
    Base class for all Alien technical exception
    VersionConflictException
    Exception happens when a4c cannot resolve version conflicts in a transparent manner for users
    VersionRenameNotPossibleException
    This exception should be thrown when a version of something is not possible since it is used in topologies.
